<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Nunjucks Assignment</title>
</head>

<body>
    <h1 style='text-align:center'>Nunjucks Queries</h1>
  <main>
      <h1>Ques.1 If Id is even print its respective name, username, email else print "I'm Odd"</h1>
    {% for item in user %}
    {% if item.id % 2 == 0 %}
    <div id="box">
   <p>Name: {{ item.name }}</p> 
   <p> Username: {{ item.username }}</p> 
   <p>Email: {{ item.email }}</p>
    {% else %}
   <li style="color:red">I'm Odd</li>
    {% endif %}
</div>
 {% endfor %}
 <h1>Ques 2. From the shared sapmle data of array JSON, based on all id values get its respecive
address keys and values and print them.</h1>

  {% for item in user %}


<li>
<b>Street:</b> {{ item.address.street }}
    <b>Suite: </b>{{ item.address.suite }}
    
   <b> City:</b> {{ item.address.city }}
   <b> Zipcode: </b>{{ item.address.zipcode }}
   <b> Geo: </b>
    Latitude: {{ item.address.geo.lat }}
    Longitude: {{ item.address.geo.lng }}
 </li>
     {% endfor %}
      <h1>Ques 3. If any email ends with .biz print its name with email values.</h1>
    {% for item in user %}

  {% if item.email.endsWith('.biz') %}
  <li> Name: {{ item.name }}</li>
  <li> Email: {{ item.email }}</li>
   
    {% endif %}
   {% endfor %}
   <h1>Ques 4. If city contains any of following "Aliyaview", "Howemouth", Gwenborough print its
respective cityname, zipcode, Geo with lat and lang values.</h1>
    {% for item in user %}

  {% if item.address.city in ["Aliyaview", "Howemouth", "Gwenborough"] %}
<li> "The Zipcode and Geo of cityname {{ item.address.city }} is: {{ item.address.zipcode }} and Latitude: {{
    item.address.geo.lat }} Longitude: {{ item.address.geo.lng }}"</li>
   
     {% endif %}

   {% endfor %}
   <h1>Ques 5. Print CatchPhrase which will contain max 15 letters.</h1>
     {% for item in user %}
    <li> CatchPhrase: {{ item.company.catchPhrase.slice(0, 15) }}</li>
   {% endfor %}
    
   
</main>
</body>

</html>
